title: For Sale/Trade:  USE COMMON SENSE
postcontent:
Ok, here we go:  

If some idiot wants to sell you a Wilson Combat, LB, EB, Nighthawk Custom...ect. For any amount for $1500 and under IT IS A SCAM!!!! Anyone who knows the least bit of information pertaining to custom/semi-custom 1911's will know that they will at the very least cost you $2500 or so used. Do not send these fools any money! 

Also, if the same idiot wants you to send him or her a check by money order and in turn he or she will send you the weapon , DONT DO IT!  It is a scam. If they insist that they are legit then have them send the prospective weapon to a FFL of your choice before you send your hard earned cash. The FFL will not release the weapon to you without authorization from the seller. Hence the seller will then need the money. That way you know that the weapon is legit, you are following the rules set by the state of MD and you will not get scammed. The sellers will rarely agree to this because they never had the weapon in the first place. SHOCKER!

We have all worked very hard to protect and defend our 2nd amendment and the last thing we need is some idiot trying to take advantage of it. 

Sorry for the long winded post but these people piss me off!

Stay safe and God bless America!
